The paper deals with covert communication over a noisy channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of the impact of an adversary on the communication, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a slotted channel model and the consideration of transmission time suggest that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM), networked systems (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
